latestPosts.caption:
Historic Win for Disability Rights in India 🇮🇳

On April 30, 2025, the Supreme Court ruled that Digital Access is a Fundamental Right under the Right to Life.

This came after Pragya Prasun’s petition highlighting the exclusion of acid attack survivors, visually impaired, elderly, and those with facial disfigurements from digital services like eKYC.

The Court issued 20+ directions to make KYC, fintech, and digital platforms inclusive for all.

This is how change happens. This is disability justice. @ministrywcd @ncwindia @vijayarahatkar
@meerfoundationofficial
#disabilityrights #disabilityjustice #acidattack #burn #atijeevan #atijeevanfoundation

Renowned Choreographer and Dancer Dr. Sandip Soparrkar @sandip_soparrkar and IME along with members of the @gaettrust @atijeevan @thevoiceofblindby @parkinsonssocietyindia @surbhirbansal @btdvipin @nalandacollegeofperformingarts @mayank_m.s.d and several individuals with mixed abilities, transformed the meaning of movement on the eve of International Dance Day.

At “Dance Is for Everybody,” resilience wore rhythm, and silence spun into song.

Barriers didn’t just break — they danced too.

This was not a show.
This was a new kind of stage.

And everybody who moved across it changed what dance can mean — forever.

Our heartfelt gratitude to the tireless efforts and dedication of team @sandipsoparrkarsballroomstudio, the participation of the talented host @ratanpratap and the support of @ifac4artist @haresh.mehta.712 @vedafactory @uma.rele and her students, @chakraborty_madhumita and @tonychakraborty 

#DanceIsForEverybody #sandipsoparrkar #IndraniMukerjeaEnterprise #InternationalDanceDay #BreakingBarriers #ResilienceInMotion #unbroken #indranimukerjea

Today was a beautiful blend of purpose and passion.

A simple black thread anklet.
A powerful story.
A future these hands will shape.

On behalf of Bindhani I could join an inspiring circle of changemakers — sharing space with the founder of Atijeevan the Pragya Prasoon Singh and creative personality Tamishra, the visionary behind her own venture Aaborran. Together, we explored the art of handmade black thread charm anklets, not just as a craft, but as a creative skill to empower our team of  women warriors.

The goal? To spark a journey where art can becomes livelihood or a skill to generate extra income for themselves.

Between sips of chai, tasty snacks, and some soulful, mindful gossip — we connected, created, and celebrated the spirit of women uplifting women.

Hope to arrange few more tea sips meeting with an advance skill sharing of silkthred wrapping, resin art, kundan embellishments.
